Multiple winners in all classes including maiden victories for D’Ambrose, Missig, Olson, Rafols, Sanderson and Tweedlie.&nbsp;

Radical Sportscars created history on the weekend, fielding the largest ever grid in North America with its flagship series, the Blue Marble Cocktails Radical Cup. However the milestones didn’t end there. The NTT IndyCar Series REV Group Grand Prix at Road America, June 20-23, also marked the first time the Radical Cup has supported America’s premier open-wheel series and featured the largest crowd to ever witness a Radical race. With action packed races and multiple race winners in every class, the Radical Cup became an instant crowd favorite and lived up to Road America’s slogan of “Road racing at its best.”
